item.description:
Certificate pinning also known as Public Key Pinning &ldquo;is a mechanism for sites to specify which certificate authorities have issued valid certs for that site, and for user-agents to reject TLS connections to those sites if the certificate is not issued by a known-good CA.&rdquo;
Sites that use certificate pinning will typically not be loaded in your browser if you are proxying it through ZAP.
In Firefox you can change the about:config pref: &lsquo;security.
